			<p class="film-content">
						In 1959, Billy Wilder directed and produced the American comedy Some Like It Hot, starring Marilyn Monroe, Tony Curtis, and Jack Lemmon. The film follows two musicians, Joe and Jerry, who witness a mob hit and flee by disguising themselves as women to enter an all-women band headed to Florida. As “Josephine” and “Daphne”, the pair try to maintain their secret identities while juggling with womanhood and romantic complications as Joe falls for the band’s singer Sugar Kane (played by Monroe), and Jerry catches the eye of an eccentric millionaire. This film is not only filled with witty dialogue and screwball comedy, but also the exploration of several progressive themes including gender identity, traditional versus conservative views, and love.
			</p>
